  "prompt": "What are good examples of websites built using Adobe ColdFusion?",
  "response": "Adobe ColdFusion is a powerful platform for building dynamic websites, often used for enterprise-level applications. Over the years, several organizations and companies have used ColdFusion to create robust websites and applications. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **NASA**: NASA has used ColdFusion for some of its internal applications and websites, taking advantage of its capabilities to handle complex data and provide reliable, scalable solutions.\n\n2. **Boeing**: The aerospace giant has used ColdFusion for various internal and external applications, demonstrating the platform's strength in handling large-scale data and security needs.\n\n3. **Lufthansa**: The German airline has utilized ColdFusion for some of its applications, leveraging its ability to build extensive and reliable booking and information systems.\n\n4. **HSBC**: This major banking institution has used ColdFusion for several web applications, showcasing its reliability and efficiency in the financial industry where security and performance are crucial.\n\n5. **Adobe.com**: Naturally, Adobe has used ColdFusion for parts of its own website, utilizing its own technology to support its digital solutions and resources.\n\nIt\u2019s worth noting that while these companies may have used ColdFusion for some applications, they might also use other technologies across their various digital platforms. ColdFusion\u2019s ease of integration with other systems makes it a versatile choice for diverse business needs.",
